# Anthropic Quickstarts (repo)

This repository is a **collection of independent quickstarts** (separate apps). There is no single install at the root: open the matching subdirectory README for setup.

## Where things live

| Path | Stack | Purpose |
|------|--------|--------|
| `agents/` | Python | Minimal Claude + tools + MCP reference agent |
| `computer-use-demo/` | Python, Docker, Streamlit | Anthropic computer-use tools + desktop loop |
| `browser-use-demo/` | Python, Docker, Playwright | Custom browser tool + sampling loop |
| `autonomous-coding/` | Python, Claude Agent SDK | Long-running initializer + coding sessions |
| `customer-support-agent/` | Next.js 14 | Support UI + Bedrock KB patterns |
| `financial-data-analyst/` | Next.js 14 | Chat + uploads + Recharts |

## CI (GitHub Actions)

`tests.yaml` runs **Ruff, Pyright, and pytest only under `computer-use-demo/`** when those paths change. Other Python trees are not gated by that workflow unless extended.

## Legal / changelog

If you edit files that include a **copyright notice**, update that subdirectory’s **`CHANGELOG.md`** (see repo `CLAUDE.md`).

## Editor / types

Root `pyproject.toml` only configures **Pyright** to use `computer-use-demo/.venv` for analysis convenience.
